cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised domain adaptation for neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a training scheme using a Transformer-based NMT model, which involves iterative back translation, a technique commonly used in machine learning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper may involve some image processing techniques, as the authors mention using images to aid in translation. This could make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper may involve some optimization techniques, as the authors aim to improve the performance of the NMT model. This could make cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a relevant sub-category as well.
